OL,3,C'It's more like a care home': The
OL,4,Cprison struggling with an ageing
OL,5,Cpopulation
OL,7,FQuiet and calm were not the words
OL,8,Fyou'd expect to describe such a
OL,9,Fsituation but that's exactly what it
OL,10,Fwas. Some sat reading newspapers,
OL,11,Fothers played pool or moved up and
OL,12,Fdown the communal area.
OL,14,FIf it wasn't for the cell doors and
OL,15,Fcoordinated inmate uniforms, you could
OL,16,Feasily believe you were inside a care
OL,17,Fhome, with most using wheelchairs and
OL,18,Fwalking aids.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/17
