OL,3,C'It's more like a care home': The
OL,4,Cprison struggling with an ageing
OL,5,Cpopulation
OL,7,FBut these are serious criminals who
OL,8,Fhave either been in prison for
OL,9,Fdecades, or convicted later in life of
OL,10,Fhistorical sexual crimes.
OL,12,FPrison Officer, Steven Zanieri said:
OL,13,F"There's a lot of people who don't
OL,14,Fwant to work (here) simply because of
OL,15,Fthe type of prisoners we've got and
OL,16,Fthe age of the prisoners we've got.
