OL,3,C'It's more like a care home': The
OL,4,Cprison struggling with an ageing
OL,5,Cpopulation
OL,7,FHe showed us a cell with bunk beds,
OL,8,Fshared by men in their 70s and 80s.
OL,9,FYou can instantly see how providing
OL,10,Fcare for mobility issues in such a
OL,11,Fsetting is almost impossible for staff.
OL,13,FColin said: "They're not getting the
OL,14,Fcare they deserve basically. They get
OL,15,Fstressed with it and we understand
OL,16,Fthat. They know there is nothing else
OL,17,Fwe can do; we are only trying our best.
OL,26,@uD@MOU
