OL,3,C'It's more like a care home': The
OL,4,Cprison struggling with an ageing
OL,5,Cpopulation
OL,7,FColin thinks this would be a good
OL,8,Fidea, saying: "You wouldn't have 70-
OL,9,Fyear-olds climbing up on bunk beds,
OL,10,Fpeople swinging hoists about in a four-
OL,11,Fby-four cell. So yes, I'd be all in
OL,12,Ffavour of that."
OL,14,FWe were shown how Glenochil has
OL,15,Fadapted some bunk bed cells to be able
OL,16,Fto contain a hospital bed but that
OL,17,Fultimately reduces a two person cell
OL,18,Fto one, when they are already running
OL,19,Fover capacity.
