OL,3,C'It's more like a care home': The
OL,4,Cprison struggling with an ageing
OL,5,Cpopulation
OL,7,F"We have a finite number of accessible
OL,8,Fcells and those that are being
OL,9,Fconverted. But those are always in
OL,10,Fdemand. I will never have an an empty,
OL,11,Faccessible cell."
OL,13,FGlenochil is designed for 670, but
OL,14,Fwith adapted cells it's closer to 650.
OL,15,FLast year the population reached 770,
OL,16,Fit now sits just over 700.
OL,18,FIf the over 60s at Glenochil were
OL,19,Fplaced in a specialised facility for
OL,20,Folder prisoners, the prison population
OL,21,Fwould sit below capacity.
