OL,3,C'It's more like a care home': The
OL,4,Cprison struggling with an ageing
OL,5,Cpopulation
OL,7,FSharanne said: "I fully appreciate
OL,8,Fsome of society's view on that, but
OL,9,Fthese people can still be safely
OL,10,Fmanaged in a far less secure
OL,11,Fenvironment, it doesn't necessarily
OL,12,Fmean that they require to be
OL,13,Faccommodated in a prison. It may be
OL,14,Fthat actually less secure facilities
OL,15,Fis an option and would be more
OL,16,Fsuitable.
