OL,3,C'It's more like a care home': The
OL,4,Cprison struggling with an ageing
OL,5,Cpopulation
OL,7,FOr indeed, is it appropriate that we
OL,8,Fmanage these people in the community,
OL,9,Fwhether it be on supervised release
OL,10,Forders, whether it would be on some
OL,11,Fform of tagging."
OL,13,FIt's controversial, but it could ease
OL,14,Fthe overburdened prison system and in
OL,15,Fturn, improve work life for staff.
OL,17,FSocial care costs would no longer need
OL,18,Fto be split across establishments,
OL,19,Finstead they could be reduced by
OL,20,Fcombining to one facility.
